What will be the output of the following C program?

void count(int n) {
    static int d = 1;
    printf("%d", n);
    printf("%d", d);
    d++;
    if (n > 1) count(n - 1);
    printf("%d", d);
}
void main() {
    count(3);
}

A. 312213444
B. 312132444
C. 312213333
D. 312112112

Consider the following program:

int f(int *p, int n) {
    if (n <= 1) return 0;
    else return max(f(p + 1, n - 1), p[0] - p[1]);
}
int main() {
    int a[] = {3, 5, 2, 6, 4};
    printf("%d", f(a, 5));
}

Note: max(x, y) returns the maximum of x and y.
The value printed by this program is ___.

A. 3
B. 4
C. 2
D. 6

